<h2>RSS feeds</h2>

<p>We offer the following RSS feeds, with links and suitable for
 copy’n’pasting directly into your favourite RSS reader (as well
 as referred to via &lt;link rel="…" …&gt; on the website):
</p><ul>
 <li style="list-style:none;">– directly from our website –</li>
 <li>Current project news: <a
  href="http://www.mirbsd.org/news.rss">http://www.mirbsd.org/news.rss</a></li>
 <li>Developers’ weblog (most recent): <a
  href="http://www.mirbsd.org/wlog.rss">http://www.mirbsd.org/wlog.rss</a></li>
 <li>Developers’ weblog (post MirOS #10): <a
  href="http://www.mirbsd.org/wlog-10.rss">http://www.mirbsd.org/wlog-10.rss</a></li>
 <li>Developers’ weblog (post MirOS #9): <a
  href="http://www.mirbsd.org/wlog-9.rss">http://www.mirbsd.org/wlog-9.rss</a></li>
 <li style="list-style:none;">– autoconverted mailing list –</li>
 <li>General discussion mailing list – for users, developers, mksh: <a
  href="http://rss.gmane.org/messages/complete/gmane.os.miros.general">http://rss.gmane.org/messages/complete/gmane.os.miros.general</a></li>
 <li>Source changes (CVS generated mails) – for developers: <a
  href="http://rss.gmane.org/messages/complete/gmane.os.miros.cvs">http://rss.gmane.org/messages/complete/gmane.os.miros.cvs</a></li>
 <li>The GMane directory entries for the <a
  href="http://dir.gmane.org/gmane.os.miros.general">discussion</a> and <a
  href="http://dir.gmane.org/gmane.os.miros.cvs">CVS</a> mailing lists offer
  additional RSS feed variants and other methods how to read the mailing lists.
 </li>
</ul>

